caption.text: I'm not a size 00. I have an ass, and curves.. And it's taken me a long time to accept this.. I've actually been told (by a MAN) that I wasn't "small enough" and he only dated "super tiny" girls. I haven't always had the body that I own now. I was a little bean pole back in the day.. 5ft 95lb girl.. But, I also didn't have the two beautiful children that I have now. I'm not fat, and I know that.. But I'm also not the tiniest thing in the world, and I'm okay with that. I will gladly take this ass, these hips and my decent sized breasts (that my lovely babies gave me) over a stick figure anyday. So, say what you want.. But you can't take away my smile,that my kids put on my face everyday, with your hateful words. | #westophate #realtalk | Join @missbrowneyes and I in this new tag to bring awareness to the different kinds of hate we endure everyday, as well as maybe help put an end to it. Take a photo, relevant to some form of hate you've dealt with in your life. Incorporate "Stop hate" in the photo somehow and tag it #westophate. In the caption, tell us your story. Thanks guys!
